    "body_text": [
        {
            "endOffset": 39635,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s000020",
            "sentence": "Maximising the compression or minimising the superstring length are dual problems (known as Maximum Compression and SSP, respectively).",
            "startOffset": 39500,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 39744,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s000020",
            "sentence": "An optimal solution for one is also optimal for the other, while good approximate solutions differ for both.",
            "startOffset": 39636,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 39935,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br000025": {
                    "endOffset": 39883,
                    "startOffset": 39880
                }
            },
            "secId": "s000020",
            "sentence": "To solve this artificial asymmetry, another definition of approximation ratio has been proposed: the differential approximation ratio  [5], which incorporates the size of the worst solution.",
            "startOffset": 39745,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 32090,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s000010",
            "sentence": "Here, we exhibit for SSP an upper bound of the superstring approximation ratio of an algorithm in function of its compression ratio.",
            "startOffset": 31958,
            "title": "Relation between maximum compression and shortest superstring approximation ratios for SSP"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 40008,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s000020",
            "sentence": "For SSP in general, there is no longest superstring (no worst solution).",
            "startOffset": 39936,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 40312,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s000020",
            "sentence": "For the Maximum Compression problem, the compression ratio is both the classical and the differential approximation ratio.",
            "startOffset": 40190,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 40527,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s000020",
            "sentence": "As we conjecture that computing a longest superstring obtained from a permutation of the input words is NP-hard, the study of the differential approximability of SSP appears as an appealing future line of research.",
            "startOffset": 40313,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 40189,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s000020",
            "sentence": "With the natural restriction we considered for Theorem 1, the superstring ratio is the classical ratio, while the compression ratio is the differential approximation ratio for SSP.",
            "startOffset": 40009,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        }
    ],
